# API Client Guidelines

## Implementation Requirements
- All API clients must implement an interface (e.g., `IBinanceApiClient`)
- Use HttpClient injected via HttpClientFactory
- Configure base URL, headers, and timeout in constructor
- Use structured logging for all operations
- Handle HTTP errors with EnsureSuccessStatusCode or custom error handling
- Handle JSON deserialization errors gracefully
- Use CancellationToken for all async operations

## Error Handling
- Log errors with appropriate log levels (Error for failures, Warning for edge cases)
- Throw meaningful exceptions that include context
- Don't swallow exceptions - let them bubble up with proper logging

## Configuration
- API credentials should come from configuration (not hardcoded)
- Support both JSON configuration files and environment variables
- Use IOptions pattern for configuration binding